h3. dmx_controller

*https://github.com/jlbrogdon/dmx_controller*

Example DMX light controller for the Raspberrypi (or any Linux box).  The controller communicates with DMX slave devices via an OpenDmxUsb device.

h4. USB DMX interface

The OpenDmxUsb hardware includes an FTDI USB-serial device and RS485 driver.  The Python *pyftdi* module (*https://github.com/eblot/pyftdi*) provides the software interface to the FTDI USB driver.

h4. LCD UI

The LCD UI is provided by Lcdproc *http://lcdproc.org*, via the lcdproc client library (*https://github.com/jingleman/lcdproc.git*).

h4. DMX Slave Device

For this example controller, I used a *Chauvet COLORstrip Mini* (*http://www.chauvetlighting.com/colorstrip-mini.html*) at DMX address 0.  The DMX channel values corresponding to the colors used in this demo are available in the COLORstrip Mini product manual: http://www.chauvetlighting.com/products/manuals/COLORstrip_-Mini_Rev03c_UM.pdf